The city of Vanport is lost forever, but many are the descendants, the old people who lived and worked there, and children who grew up there---still living in and around Portland, sharing their photographs and memories. That is the basis for this book. They tell of an otherwise forgotten city.

On Memorial Day 1948 an Oregon city of more than 18,000 residents was swept away in a matter of hours. Manly Maben's "Vanport" does an outstanding job of telling the story of the swift rise and astonishing destruction of the largest World War II housing project in the United States.
